          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "code": "XCTContext",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " provides a way for activities (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.xctest/documentation/XCTest/XCTActivity",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ") to run against the current testing context, either directly in a test case or in custom testing utilities. You can break up long test methods in UI tests or integration tests into activities to reuse, and to simplify results in the Xcode test reports. Use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.xctest/documentation/XCTest/XCTContext/runActivity(named:block:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to run a block of code as a named substep in a test. For more information, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.xctest/documentation/XCTest/grouping-tests-into-substeps-with-activities",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
